SECTION 6: TULLY-FISHER RELATION
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  MOND a0                                  1.2e-10
  c*H0/(2*pi)                              1.0420889946e-10
  a0 / [c*H0/(2*pi)]                       1.1515331284
  [PASS] MOND a0 ~ c*H0/(2*pi) within factor 2
        ratio = 1.152

  The MOND acceleration a0 ~ c*H0/(2*pi) to within ~15.2%.
  In R2 language: a0 ~ c*H0/(8*R2) since 2*pi = 8*R2.
  This connects the DM acceleration scale to the Hubble rate
  through the same R2 geometry appearing in 15+ domains.
  c*H0/(8*R2)                              1.0420889946e-10
  [PASS] a0 in R2 form equals a0 in 2*pi form
        identity: 8*R2 = 2*pi

  Baryonic Tully-Fisher: M_baryon = v^4 / (G * a0)
  With a0 = c*H0/(8*R2): M_baryon = 8*R2*v^4 / (G*c*H0)
  The R2 factor connects Tully-Fisher to the soliton geometry.

